#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:3
msgid "Community Engagement Guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:5
msgid ""
"Below is a list of guidelines for maintainers, key contributors and "
"Mattermost, Inc. staff to use when engaging with the broader community in"
" forums, GitHub issues, Twitter, our Mattermost servers and other places "
"of online conversation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:8
msgid "Best Practices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:11
msgid "1. Don't offer advice on database modification without a clear warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:13
msgid "Never give DB advice without a warning similar to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:15
msgid ""
"``Manual database modification bypasses checks in the code and could make"
" a system unrecoverable. It's not recommended and if you do make a "
"change, make sure to back up your DB, and verify changes carefully.``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:18
msgid "2. Answer with docs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:20
msgid ""
"When answering a common question, always include a link to the docs so "
"the person asking--along with people in future who read your response--"
"has a reference. If no doc exists, do one of two things:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:22
msgid ""
"Add the documentation, then answer the question with a link to the "
"information, or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:23
msgid ""
"Answer the question and open a ticket for the missing information to be "
"added to docs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:25
msgid ""
"During the triage process, if the information missed should have "
"obviously been included, assign the ticket to the last approver for the "
"doc PR, otherwise assign to doc PR author."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:28
msgid "3. Avoid speculation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:30
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Circumstances change frequently. Don't set expectations for something "
"that you're not 100% sure will happen. If it doesn't happen, people will "
"be more upset than if you didn't say anything."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:32
msgid ""
"For example, if you haven't seen a feature merged into a specific product"
" in a specific edition, don't tell people the feature will be in until "
"you see it merged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:37
msgid "Speaking in the Voice of Mattermost"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:39
msgid ""
"Mattermost serves a global audience, who might not use English as their "
"first language."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:41
msgid ""
"To keep Mattermost “obvious” to users, please keep community discussion, "
"documentation and on-screen help simple, effective and ready-to-"
"translate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:43
msgid "**Simple**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:45
msgid ""
"Aim for the reading ability of an 11-year old. Use short sentences. Avoid"
" large words."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:47
msgid "**Effective**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:49
msgid ""
"Start with what’s important, and leave less important details to the end,"
" or omit them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:50
msgid ""
"Focus on achieving understanding in the reader, over total correctness or"
" completeness."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:52
msgid "**Ready-to-translate**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:54
msgid "Avoid slang."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:55
msgid ""
"Avoid Western-centric, or culture-centric examples (example: instead of "
"“fiddle with settings”, say “adjust settings”)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:57
msgid ""
"If you’re not sure, try using machine translation to turn your content "
"into a foreign language then back into English."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:60
msgid "Machine-Translation Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:62
msgid ""
"Here’s an example of culture-specific content with the word “fiddle” "
"(meaning “to adjust repeatedly”):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:64
msgid ""
"There are a few configuration settings you might want to fiddle with when"
" setting up your instance of Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:66
msgid ""
"That documentation machine-translated into German and then back into "
"English looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:68
msgid ""
"There are some configuration settings you could know if your instance "
"Matter Most violin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:70
msgid ""
"The sentence would be more ready-to-translate to say “There are a few "
"configuration settings you can adjust when setting up your instance of "
"Mattermost.”"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:73
msgid "Testing our documentation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:75
msgid ""
"One technique to use to review content is to ask: “How would Agent "
"Coulson explain this concept to Thor?” [1]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:77
msgid ""
"Agent Coulson takes complex ideas and explains them simply and "
"effectively. Thor isn’t from earth, so we have to filter out ideas that "
"are culturally specific-–fiddles, baseball, wedding rings, etc.--and that"
" makes things easy-to-translate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:79
msgid ""
"As a communications company, clarity matters. If you see content that "
"doesn't speak in the \"Voice of Mattermost\", we’d gladly accept issue "
"reports and pull requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/community.rst:81
msgid ""
"[1] This example relies on knowledge of the 2012 movie \"Avengers\", "
"which we consider a \"global\" reference, not a culture-specific "
"reference, since it achieved `record-breaking sales "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Avengers_(2012_film)>`__ around the "
"world--in the United States, Mexico, Brazil, Ecuador, Bolivia, Taiwan, "
"the Philippines, Hong Kong, the United Arab Emirates, Argentina, Peru and"
" Central America, among other regions."
msgstr ""

